<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<bibRefCitation author="Leandri, J" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Systematicae" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" refId="B39" refString="Leandri, J, 1970b. Quatre Croton nouveaux du sud de Madagascar (Euphorbiacees). Adansonia, ser. 2, 10: 183-190." title="Quatre Croton nouveaux du sud de Madagascar (Euphorbiacees). Adansonia, ser. 2, 10: 183 - 190." year="1970 b">Leandri (1970b)</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Cours 4641</emphasis>
as the holotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. aubrevilecta" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" rank="species" species="aubrevilecta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">C. aubrevilecta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but there are three sheets of this collection at P. One of them, P00312369, has a label in Leandri's handwriting saying 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“type,”">&quot;type,&quot;</normalizedToken>
and the other two duplicates at P have labels stating 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“isotype.”">&quot;isotype.&quot;</normalizedToken>
The isotypes at P have preprinted labels stating 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Itinéraire">&quot;Itineraire</normalizedToken>
de Didy 
<normalizedToken originalValue="à">a</normalizedToken>
Brickaville (
<normalizedToken originalValue="forêt">foret</normalizedToken>
orientale),&quot; but P00380444 has a note added later stating 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Localité">&quot;Localite</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="très">tres</normalizedToken>
douteuse, voir 
<normalizedToken originalValue="récolte">recolte</normalizedToken>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Homolle 1944</emphasis>
(avec 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M.G. Cours</emphasis>
).&quot; The holotype has a penciled note stating &quot;Probablement 
<normalizedToken originalValue="région">region</normalizedToken>
de Tranoroa.&quot; In the protologue, 
<bibRefCitation author="Leandri, J" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Systematicae" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" refId="B39" refString="Leandri, J, 1970b. Quatre Croton nouveaux du sud de Madagascar (Euphorbiacees). Adansonia, ser. 2, 10: 183-190." title="Quatre Croton nouveaux du sud de Madagascar (Euphorbiacees). Adansonia, ser. 2, 10: 183 - 190." year="1970 b">Leandri (1970b)</bibRefCitation>
also alluded to the erroneous labels from Didy and states that the collection likely came from far southern Madagascar close to Lake Tsimanampetsotsa.
</paragraph>
